oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Aluminum dog tag of Pvt. Ernest D. Warlick
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Pvt. Ernest D. Warlick of Spring Creek in Madison County, Tennessee, wore this dog tag during his service in World War I. He worked on the railroads and served in Co. A, 13th Engineers in France, first in Verdun and later at Meuse-Argonne. He was a railroad brakeman before the war and lived in Jackson after the war. According to his May 8, 1919 discharge papers, he was 5'11" tall, with blue eyes, light brown hair and a ruddy complexion.
